The paper deals with privacy concerns in mobile healthcare systems, which involves the collection and release of sensitive health data. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed approach also involves the use of algorithms for data partitioning and privacy preservation, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of simulations and experiments to test the accuracy of the proposed approach, which could be related to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
